title: Manage materials HCAIM
description: HCAIM uses SURFsharekit for sharing materials and Wikiwijs Maken for creating lesson plans based on the material.

Cooperation

The Master's degree 'Human Centered AI' was developed in a partnership of 4 universities and was co-funded by the Connecting Europe Facility of the European Union under Grant №CEF-TC-2020-1 Digital Skills 2020-EU-IA-0068.

More than 150 lesson plans have been developed. Most lesson plans contain materials in various formats (e.g. PowerPoint, Excel, PDF, HTML, ipynb)

Usage

The lesson plans for the master, including developed materials, are accessible and usable by students and teachers without logging in. Lesson plans and materials can be found via the HCAIM website and in searchable form via Edusources.

Management

The content of these lesson plans and the materials can be maintained by employees of all participating universities. To this end, they must be able to register with SURFsharekit and Wikiwijs. Access to the management environments can then be requested.

• To log in to SURFsharekit or Wikiwijs, a SURF account or a personal EduID account is required . Creating an EduID will be particularly necessary if foreign colleagues are going to manage the lesson plans or materials.
  • Create EduID (Dutch)
  • Create EduID (English)
  • It is then important that the SURF account or EduID in question has access to the HCAIM Consortium environments in SURFsharekit and Wikiwijs.

Access to the HCAIM Consortium in SURFsharekit

  • How do you request access to a service? I can imagine that not everyone can request this from SURF, but that it is done, for example, through an HCAIM administrator to be appointed. And he could then contact SURF. Is there a procedure for that? Who has the rights to add people/accounts? Is that Dafne?

Access to the HCAIM Consortium team in Wikiwijs

  • Send a request for access by email to <HCAIM team manager>
  • The administrator sends an invitation by email with an acceptance link.
  • Click on the acceptance link.
  • Register now. the next screen appears:

  • Now enter SURF in the window and then select SURF
  • The next screen appears. Search for your own institution or 'EduID' and log in.

  • If this is the first time that a user logs in to Wikiwijs, an input screen will be shown and the first name, last name and email address must be entered once. (if this information is already known, the HCAIM consortium team will be contacted directly)
  • Agree to the terms and conditions and click 'Save'
  • An email will now be sent to the specified email address, containing a confirmation link. By clicking on this in the same browser in which you logged in, the first registration is completed and the Wikiwijs account is activated.
  • The HCAIM consortium team is now being reached.

• Go to surfsharekit.nl . The next screen appears. Click on login.

  • The next screen appears. Choose your own institution or EduID here and log in.

  • After logging in, the dashboard will appear . Select 'publications ' on the left.
  • The ' publications ' screen appears. All publications for which the user in question has received metadata rights are shown here. All publications made by the HCAIM consortium can be found here.

• Go to https://mijn.wikiwijs.nl
  • The following screen is displayed.

  • Now enter SURF in the window and then select SURF
  • The next screen appears. Search for your own institution here or register via EduID.

  • The next screen appears. Go to 'my teams' here ( 'mijn teams')..

  • Click on the team named HCAIM Consortium

  • By default, the 'arrangements' (arrangementen) section is already selected. The folder layout of the lesson plans is shown here. By opening the relevant folder, the underlying arrangements (lesson plans) become visible.

The HCAIM master has 4 modules (A to D) and is divided into 3 aspects (technical, practical and ethical). A large number of lesson plans have been developed for the HCAIM master. Every lesson plan has the same, fixed structure. Each lesson plan indicates which module and which aspect it belongs to. Most lesson plans include one or more materials. These materials can be text files, presentations, program code, and so on.

  1. The materials, organized by lesson plan, are included in SURFsharekit. Each lesson plan has one publication record in SURFsharekit.
  2. The lesson plans are designed as a 'website' in Wikiwijs. The unique link to the lesson plan will be included in the corresponding publication record.
  3. The publication records in SURFsharekit are provided with metadata. Important here are:
    1. title. This is the title of the corresponding lesson plan.
    2. resume. Here the learning objectives are taken from the corresponding lesson plan
    3. keywords. Various characteristics of the material are recorded here: including module, focus and theme, supplemented with specific keywords for the lesson plan.
    4. files. The materials associated with the relevant lesson plan are included here
    5. left. The link to the lesson plan is included here
  4. The unique links to the lesson plans are included in an overview, also created in Wikiwijs. The lesson plans are presented organized by module and focus. The overview is included on the HCAIM website .

The lesson plans + materials included in SURFsharekit are also available in a searchable form via the Edusources search portal.

• Go to SURFsharekit and register.
  • Go to publications
  • Find the publication record you want to change or delete. You can find the desired publication record by typing part of the title or keyword in the search bar.

Edit publication record

It may be necessary to edit the publication record in SURFsharekit. For example, because a newer version of the material is available or because the metadata needs to be adjusted.

  • Click on the relevant publication record to display the contents of the record.
  • The 'edit' button now becomes visible at the top right. Click to change the contents of the record. All metadata included with the publication record now becomes visible one below the other.

Files and links

Please note: it is possible to replace an uploaded file with a newer version. This ensures that the lesson plan containing the file in question continues to work normally, but now shows the new version of the file.

It is also possible to delete an uploaded file . The lesson plan in which this file was shown now contains a dead link: the file is no longer available. In this case, this link should also be removed from the lesson plan in Wikiwijs.

It is possible to add a new file. This file has not previously been shown in the lesson plan. The link to the new file must be added to the lesson plan in Wikiwijs.

  • Click on the pencil behind the title of the file to upload a new version
  • Click on the recycle bin behind the name of the file to delete this file (remember to also adjust the lesson plan in Wikiwijs)
  • Click the plus button or drag your files to add new files (don't forget to adjust the lesson plan in Wikiwijs)

Important

Adjustments to the metadata entered here will affect the findability of the material. In any case, keep the keywords that relate to the module, theme or focus.

To publish

PLEASE NOTE: after clicking the 'change' button, your publication record will automatically be given draft status. Once you have completed your changes, click 'publish' to keep the published status.
If you do not want to publish the record, click 'save' when you are done.

Delete publication record

Please note: by deleting a publication record, all materials and the lesson plan will no longer be found. However, the lesson plan itself still exists. If this also needs to be removed, this can be done via the HCAIM environment in Wikiwijs.

  • click on the relevant publication record to display the contents of the record.
  • The recycle bin now becomes visible at the top right. Click to delete the record.
  • A warning message will appear.
  • Click 'confirm' to delete the record.

• Go to mijn.wikiwijs.nl and register.
  • Select 'HCAIM Consortium' under 'my teams' (mijn teams)
  • The next screen appears. The lesson plans are organized in folders per module. In addition, a folder is visible for templates and for the overview.

  • Open the folder of the correct module. The lesson plans that belong to the module in question become visible.

  • Click on the lesson plan in which changes need to be made. The elements that make up the lesson plan are shown.

  • Find the section you want to make changes to and click on it.
  • Make the changes and click 'save'

Add link

When new material needs to be added to the lesson plan, this material is uploaded to SURFsharekit and published. The link to the relevant material must then be included in the relevant lesson plan.

Copy link from Edusources

  • Search for the material in Edusources by typing the title.
  • Click on the material to view the details.
  • Click on the yellow button to make the materials visible.
  • Right-click on the new file and copy the link.

Include link in lesson plan in Wikiwijs

  • Within the lesson plan, go to the 'lesson materials' section and click on it to open the section

  • Type the name of the file in the appropriate place.

  • Select the name and click to add the link. The next screen appears. Copy the link to the new file here.

  • Then go to the 'target window' (doelvenster) tab and choose 'new window' (nieuw venster). Then click 'ok'
  • You will return to the 'lesson materials' section. Click 'save' (opslaan) here.

It is of course possible that more lesson plans will need to be added to the master HCAIM in the future. This means that a publication record is created in SURFsharekit for each new lesson plan and is provided with metadata. The materials of the new lesson plan will then be uploaded here and the link to the lesson plan will also be included in Wikiwijs.

Working with a template

Each publication record created through the HCAIM Consortium has certain characteristics. Sometimes these are unique to the relevant publication record / lesson plan, but sometimes they involve characteristics that are the same for every publication record, such as the name of the publisher, the type of material and for whom the material is intended. To speed up the entry of the metadata, a template has been created for the HCAIM material in which the following metadata fields have already been filled:

  • the keywords: HCAIM, artificial intelligence and AI
  • the publication date 1-9-2023 (this will be cleared after September)
  • publisher: HCAIM consortium
  • field of study: interdisciplinary
  • level: HBO master, WO master
  • Language: English
  • usage rights: cc-by-sa
  • authors: HCAIM consortium
  • usable as: lesson
  • type of reading material: source of information
  • technical format: website
  • intended end user: student

A lot of time is saved by first copying the contents of this template to the new publication record to be created.

  • Go to SURFsharekit and register.
  • Go to publications
  • Click on 'add publication' and choose HCAIM Consortium if necessary. The following screen appears. Choose learning material and click on 'use template' at the bottom.

  • Enter 'the template HCAIM '. The template is now shown
  • Select the template and click ' confirm' .
  • A publication record now becomes visible in which all values ​​from the template have been copied.

Step 1: Uploads

In the step 1 uploads screen , one or more files and links can be added.

Adding files
  • Under files , drag (if applicable) the file or files associated with the new lesson plan or click the plus and select from your device's file format. After the file has been selected or dragged to the right place, a popup will appear.
  • In the popup, indicate the name of the file ( the name as used in the lesson plan ) and the right of use ( publicly accessible ). Please note: the maximum size of an added file is 500 MB.

  • Click ' Save '. The popup closes and the added file becomes visible.
    Note: If multiple files are added, the order of these files can easily be changed by dragging them to the correct position.

Add links

  • Click (if applicable) on the plus sign 'add links' to add a link to the teaching material.
  • A popup will appear. Include the url, the url name and the access rights of the teaching material.
  • Then click 'Save'. The popup closes and the added link becomes visible.

Note: If multiple links are added, the order of these links can easily be changed by dragging them to the correct order.

Next step

  • Are all files and links added, click 'next step' on the bottom of the screen

Step 2: data

Step 2 Data appears. On the bottom of the screen the progress of the metadata-process is shown. A lot of information from step 2 has already been entered via the template. Only data that must be filled in by yourself of that may need to be supplemented is mentioned here.

General data

  • Enter the title and a meaningful, brief summary of the teaching material. A subtitle may be added if preferred.
  • Fill if needed extra keywords. Keywords can be specified comma separated. After <enter> or clicking on the + sign, the keywords are saved separately.
  • Three keywords have already been entered via the template. Some lesson plans contain 'keywords'. These keywords can be adopted as keywords. This improves the findability of the specific lesson plan.
  • Keywords can be entered comma separated. After <enter> or clicking on the + sign, the keywords are saved separately.
  • Author/person involved. 'HCAIM Consortium' has already been included via the template. In many cases, the lesson plan does not include an individual author. If this is the case, it can be added.
  • Click + to add an author/person involved if desired. A popup screen will appear.
    Find the correct author on the screen.If desired, you can search outside your own organization by checking the 'search outside institution' checkbox.
  • Click the plus sign to add an author/involved person. A popup screen will appear.
  • In the screen, search for the correct author.
  • If desired, search outside your own organization by checking the 'Include other organisations' box.
  • Select the author concerned. You will now be asked to select a role. Select the correct role and click on 'save'.

  • If the author's details are not (yet) known within SURFsharekit, they can be added by clicking on 'manual'.

  • Fill in the details and click 'next'. Name, email and organisation are mandatory. Is the email address of the author/person involved unknown, then select 'I don't know what the email adress of this person is'.
  • Click next/save to add the author/involved person.

Note: if several authors/involved persons are entered, it is possible to change the order in which these authors are displayed by dragging the lines.

Next step

Are alle data entered, click 'next step' on the bottom of the screen.

The Step 3: publishing screen is reached. Here you can indicate through which portals and by when the material will be found.

  • To make materials searchable through SURF's search portal and through Wikiwijs, under channels, set the edusources slider to 'on'.
  • Under the heading 'publish on', you can specify a date on which the material must be retrievable. If you leave the date blank, the material will be published as soon as possible. If edusources & Wikiwijs is selected, the material can be found within a few minutes via SURF's search portal.
  • Enter a publication date if applicable.
  • Click on 'publish'.
    • If not all required fields have been completed, a message will appear. If you scroll back to the beginning of the record, an annotation of the mandatory metadata that is still missing will be displayed.
    • If all mandatory metadata is present, a message that publication was successful will appear after clicking 'publish'.
  • Ga to dashboard of add new publication.

It is of course possible that more lesson plans will need to be added to the master HCAIM in the future. Every new lesson plan is included in Wikiwijs Maken according to a fixed format. It then links to the materials uploaded to SURFsharekit.

  • Go to mijn.wikiwijs.nl and register.
  • Select 'HCAIM Consortium' under 'my teams' (mijn teams)
  • The next screen appears. The lesson plans are organized in folders per module. In addition, a folder is visible for templates and for the overview.
  • Open the templates and components folder.
  • Click on the 'duplicate' icon behind 'template lesson plan'. A copy of the template is now placed
  • Open the copy of the Lesson plan template. You will be asked whether the link with the source file should be retained. Click 'no' (nee) here.
  • Go to the 'properties' tab (eigenschappen) and change the name. The name is made up of <function>: <title>, for example 'Tutorial: Understanding data'. Then click 'save' (opslaan).
  • Go to the 'content' tab and open the different parts of the lesson plan one by one. Complete the sections and click 'save' (opslaan).

Add link

The lesson plans generally include many links. In some cases these will be links from an external website. In other cases, these are links to materials that are part of the master and that have been uploaded to SURFsharekit. The link to the relevant material must then be included in the relevant lesson plan.

If it concerns an external website, the link can easily be copied. How this can then be included in the lesson plan is described below.

If it concerns links to material from the master (learning materials), the links can be requested via Edusources.

Copy link from Edusources

  • Search for the material in Edusources by typing the title.
  • Click on the material to view the details.
  • Click on the yellow button to make the materials visible.
  • Right-click on the new file and copy the link.

Include link in lesson plan in Wikiwijs

  • Within the lesson plan, go to the 'lesson materials' section and click on it to open the section.

  • Type the name of the file in the appropriate place.

  • Select the name and click to add the link. The next screen appears. Copy the link to the new file here.

  • Then go to the 'target window' (doelvenster) tab and choose 'new window' (nieuw venster). Then click 'ok'
  • You will return to the 'lesson materials' section. Click 'save' )pslaan) here.

Publish 'link only'

Once the lesson plan is completely filled in, it can be published internally. This means that the lesson plan is not (yet) found by search platforms, but a unique link is generated.

  • Go to the 'publish' tab (5. publiceren)
  • Make sure 'link only' (alleen met link) is clicked
  • Then click 'publish' (publiceren). A message appears.

  • Click 'publish' (publiceren) to generate a unique link.

  • Copy the link. Go to the correct record in SURFsharekit and paste the link in the 'links' section.

Move to the correct folder

The lesson plan is now still in the folder that also contains the template. It still needs to be moved to the folder of the correct module.

  • In the overview screen of arrangements (in the templates and components folder), click on 'actions' (acties) and then on 'move' (verplaatsen)
  • Check boxes become visible for the titles of the lesson plans. Check the box for the material that needs to be moved.
  • Then click 'execute' (uitvoeren). The various Wikiwijs environments of which you are a member are displayed. Under 'my teams' (mijn teams), click open HCAIM Consortium. The folders will now become visible. Select the correct folder and click 'save' (opslaan).
  • The following message appears: 'The selected material has been moved successfully'.

heading.content: View the materials as a user

items.content:
Registration is not required to view and use the material.

The materials can be achieved in different ways.

Overview

An overview is available of all materials classified by module and focus (technical, practical, ethical). Overview HCAIM lesson plans

Search via Edusources

  • Go to https://edusources.nl
  • Choose 'search learning material'.
  • The next screen is reached. All lesson plans can be found here.
  • Edusources can be searched using a combination of filters and keywords.
    • HCAIM consortium can be selected as a filter under 'publisher'
    • This can be combined with keywords. Keywords for all materials is in any case the focus (technical focus, practical focus, ethical focus), the theme and the module (module A, module B, module C, module D).
  • An overview screen of the results found will then be shown. Click on one of the titles to see more details.
  • The full description is shown via the details screen, as well as the other entered metadata.
  • The lesson plan (including the materials) and each material separately can be requested. To do this, click on the yellow 'view materials' button.
